SSyynnooppssiiss
       cc [options] files -liaf #include <iaf.h>

       int invoke (int fd, char *command);

DDeessccrriippttiioonn
       invoke  is  a library function that invokes authentication
       schemes within the framework  of  the  Identification  and
       Authentication Facility (IAF).

       fd  indicates  the file descriptor of the connection to be
       authenticated.  command is  the  command  string  used  to
       invoke  the  scheme.   command can contain either a scheme
       tag or a full pathname.  If it is a tag, a  full  pathname
       to  the  default  IAF  directory  is generated.  In either
       case, command can contain optional  scheme-specific  argu-
       ments.

       If the scheme succeeds, a value of 0 is returned.

RReettuurrnn vvaalluueess
       invoke  returns  -1 if the scheme aborts or cannot be exe-
       cuted; otherwise, it returns the exit value of the scheme:
       0 for success and non-zero for failure.

